    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-10T15:55:45+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-10T15:55:45+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-10T06:25:45Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-10T06:25:45Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front in the Bight will move across the south of SA during Saturday followed by a weaker front on Monday. A high pressure system centred near southern WA will begin to dominate the weather pattern across SA mid next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-10T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-10T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers east of Ceduna, becoming less likely later tonight. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the late afternoon then becoming north to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the late evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers east of Ceduna, medium chance elsewhere. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h shifting southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h in the morning then tending west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 16.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 12:00pm to 1:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-12T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-11T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the late morning and afternoon. Winds westerly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the evening then becoming west to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-13T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-14T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-12T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-13T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers east of Ceduna, medium chance elsewhere. Winds west to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending west to southwesterly during the day then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-07-14T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-15T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-13T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-14T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog west of Ceduna. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Light winds becoming southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
